  "prompt": "How can someone subscribe to Facebook topics on Quora?",
  "response": "To subscribe to Facebook topics on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log into Quora**: Make sure you are signed in to your Quora account.\n\n2. **Search for Facebook Topics**: Use the search bar at the top of the page and type in \u201cFacebook\u201d or any specific topic related to Facebook that you want to follow.\n\n3. **Select the Topic**: Once you find the relevant topic in the search results, click on it to go to the topic page.\n\n4. **Follow the Topic**: On the topic page, you will see a \u201cFollow\u201d button (or \u201cFollow Topic\u201d) near the top of the page. Click this button to subscribe to the topic.\n\n5. **Manage Your Subscriptions**: Once you are following the topic, you will start receiving updates and recommendations related to it in your feed. You can manage your subscriptions through your profile settings if you ever want to unfollow the topic.\n\nBy following these steps, you'll be able to stay updated with questions, answers, and discussions related to Facebook on Quora.",
